	<Title>
		No pain, no gain? No way!
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;When it comes to exercise, the &apos;no pain, no gain&apos; mantra is bad advice. Exercise shouldn&apos;t hurt. At most, you may feel a little muscle soreness when you do a new workout or activity. If you feel pain during exercise (or dizziness, nausea or shortness of breath), stop. You may be pushing yourself too hard.&lt;/p&gt;
